member.name: T:System.Runtime.CompilerServices.ScriptAssemblyAttribute
member.summary: Marks an assembly as a script assembly that can be used with Script#. Additionally, each script must have a unique name that can be used as a dependency name. This name is also used to generate unique names for internal types defined within the assembly. The ScriptQualifier attribute can be used to provide a shorter name if needed.

member.name: T:System.Runtime.CompilerServices.ScriptQualifierAttribute
member.summary: Provides a prefix to use when generating types internal to this assembly so that they can be unique within a given a script namespace. The specified prefix overrides the script name provided in the ScriptAssembly attribute.

member.name: T:System.Runtime.CompilerServices.IgnoreNamespaceAttribute
member.summary: This attribute indicates that the namespace of type within a system assembly should be ignored at script generation time. It is useful for creating namespaces for the purpose of c# code that don't exist at runtime.

member.name: T:System.Runtime.CompilerServices.ScriptNamespaceAttribute
member.summary: Specifies the namespace that should be used in generated script. The script namespace is typically a short name, that is often shared across multiple assemblies. The developer is responsible for ensuring that public types across assemblies that share a script namespace are unique. For internal types, the ScriptQualifier attribute can be used to provide a short prefix to generate unique names.

member.name: T:System.Runtime.CompilerServices.ResourcesAttribute

member.name: T:System.Runtime.CompilerServices.GlobalMethodsAttribute

member.name: T:System.Runtime.CompilerServices.NamedValuesAttribute
member.summary: This attribute marks an enumeration type within a system assembly as as a set of names. Rather than the specific value, the name of the enumeration field is used as a string.

member.name: T:System.Runtime.CompilerServices.NumericValuesAttribute
member.summary: This attribute marks an enumeration type within a system assembly as as a set of numeric values. Rather than the enum field, the value of the enumeration field is used as a literal.

member.name: T:System.Runtime.CompilerServices.AlternateSignatureAttribute
member.summary: This attribute allows defining an alternate method signature that is not generated into script, but can be used for defining overloads to enable optional parameter semantics for a method. It must be applied on a method defined as extern, since an alternate signature method does not contain an actual method body.

member.name: T:System.Runtime.CompilerServices.IntrinsicPropertyAttribute
member.summary: This attribute denotes a C# property that manifests like a field in the generated JavaScript (i.e. is not accessed via get/set methods). This is really meant only for use when defining OM corresponding to native objects exposed to script.

member.name: T:System.Runtime.CompilerServices.ScriptNameAttribute

member.name: T:System.Runtime.CompilerServices.PreserveCaseAttribute

member.name: T:System.Runtime.CompilerServices.PreserveNameAttribute
member.summary: This attribute allows suppressing the default behavior of minimizing private type names and member names in the generated JavaScript.

member.name: T:System.Runtime.CompilerServices.ScriptAliasAttribute
member.summary: This attribute allows specifying a script name for an imported method. The method is interpreted as a global method. As a result it this attribute only applies to static methods.
